Re: Changes to Hate zone in Aggro (Not the hate revamp</span><hr size=1> We went up to do some light bits and pieces farming (and hopefully get Swaran a lute from Maestro) with a single group. No aggro on zone in, or loitering (group was .. Hm. I think our cleric was 58. Everyone else over 60. I was playing Sutekh, so 61 monk pulling).<br>
<br>
Deathrot Knight was up. I've found he causes the most problem. He's got a massive awareness range, and a bigger assist range. Oddly, at least this time, I had to actually get line of sight (going north from zonein until across from his spawnpoint and in sight of the spiral up to the second floor) before he aggroed, but as he followed he pulled (at least, they came too by chain aggro) every single damned thing I'd left up in every building anywhere near zonein.<br>
I think I came about halfway back to zi, and feigned with a monster pile on me. Which promptly took off for zonein and gave the group a slightly unhoppy welcome.<br>
<br>
With the Knight down, aggro seems about normal. With the Knight up, chain aggro can be truly evil and far more irritating than normal (I believe it's him that causes a lot of the zonein fruityness some of the lower leveled guilds are facign right now). And yes, there are some mobs that get stuck slightly out of place, and can add unusually (there are, in the building directly to the left as you look out of the zonin room, a handfull of spite golems on the second level of the house... they never came out for me, without encouragement, but I imagine if they were 'sticking through' the wall at all, they'd path to you dragging every single thing in the immediate area in. There have to be other examples of the same things.)<br>
<br>
